Empirical data on Aedes aegypti’s and albopictus’s egg hatching success (in the model
c ˙
) is taken from ( Dickerson, 2007). Data includes measurements of hatching for 5 different temperatures above 15 Celsius, including 2 wild and 1 laboratory populations for each of the vector-species. Fitting implemented with a third degree polynomial. When modelling, negative proportions below 10 Celsius are manually corrected to zero (left of shaded grey line).
